The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Aptech to enter Brazil

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, April 17: Aptech Limited is all set to enter Brazil this year and will develop content in Portuguese for the first time. The company has identified South Africa, the Philippines and Malaysia as the three key foreign locations for maximum growth opportunities this year.

 The company is also in talks to acquire US-based learning services company which develops software training content for companies based in that country. A consultant has been appointed and the deal is expected to be sealed within this quarter.

 We were in talks for some 

 time but expect to close the deal soon. We are looking at 

 US-based companies servicing local clients there with delivery 

 centres, said Pramod Khera, Chief Executive Officer 

 and Managing Director of Aptech Ltd.




